<main class="about-container">
  <header class="about-hero">
    <h1>About Cine Inventory App</h1>
    <p>How and why I created this app, and what it does.</p>
  </header>

  <section class="about-content">
    <div class="project-description">
      <h2>Project Overview</h2>
      <p>
        This project is part of the
        <strong>Full Stack JavaScript</strong> curriculum from
        <a
          href="https://www.theodinproject.com/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="odin-link"
        >
          The Odin Project </a
        >.
      </p>
      <p>
        The goal was to create an
        <strong>inventory management application</strong> for an imaginary
        store. Users can browse categories (like <strong>Films</strong> and
        <strong>Genres</strong>), view items, and perform all
        <strong>CRUD operations</strong> (Create, Read, Update, Delete) on both
        items and categories.
      </p>
      <p>
        This project helped me strengthen my skills in
        <strong>Node.js</strong>, <strong>Express</strong>,
        <strong>EJS templating</strong>, and <strong>PostgreSQL</strong> for
        database management.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="main-features">
      <h2>Main Features</h2>
      <p>
        The application includes three main pages, each designed to manage
        different aspects of the movie inventory:
      </p>
      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li>
          🎬 <strong>Movies Page:</strong> View all movies in the inventory, add
          a new movie, or modify/delete existing ones.
        </li>
        <li>
          🏷️ <strong>Genres Page:</strong> Manage genre tags associated with
          films. Users can create or delete genres, and view all films linked to
          a specific genre. Deleting a genre automatically removes it from all
          associated movies.
        </li>
        <li>
          🔍 <strong>Search Page:</strong> Search for movies based on various
          criteria such as title, director name, genre, or release year etc.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <br />
      <p>
        Additionally, from any of these pages, users can click on a movie to
        view detailed information, including all related data, and make changes
        or delete it if needed.
      </p>
    </div>

